Maybe just implement our own mini-markup language and have
simple translation into HTML and LaTeX, could be easier and 
simpler than trying to adapt and adopt existing solutions.
(Where other than TAM/CoW, there is no Java-Based solution
for Markup->Latex anyways).

Just choose a subset of Creole1.0 (http://www.wikicreole.org/wiki/Creole1.0)
for now:

See file MARKUP.txt



Now, 2013, CoW (GateWiki) seems to still be the only Java software
that can convert a lightweight markup language into either HTML 
or Latex

Maybe interesting as alternative/additional template engine:
  http://velocity.apache.org/engine/releases/velocity-1.5/user-guide.html

